<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-24T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-24T10:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Biddle, Anthony J. D./236:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Deputy Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                    Bordeaux</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-24T11:00:00-04:00">June
                                        24, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>34. Your 68, June 22, 11 a.m. Your designation as representative near
                                the French Government was special and for the emergency period
                                during the time the French Government was separated from the capital
                                by military necessity. The President now desires that you proceed to
                                Bilbao or some other point in Spain until such time as you may find
                                it possible to arrange safe transportation to England in order to
                                resume your post near the Polish Government.</p>
                            <p>We will telegraph later instructions regarding the staff.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>